umCommonInventoryTable.name: umCommonInventoryTable
umCommonInventoryTable.description: A table containing common inventory information.

umCommonInventoryModel.name: umCommonInventoryModel
umCommonInventoryModel.description: This variable indicates the model number.

umCommonInventorySwVer.name: umCommonInventorySwVer
umCommonInventorySwVer.description: This variable indicates the software version. format: a.bcd (a, b, c, d: 0 ~ 9)

umCommonInventoryHwVer.name: umCommonInventoryHwVer
umCommonInventoryHwVer.description: This variable indicates the hardware version. format: a.bcd (a, b, c, d: 0 ~ 9)

umCommonInventoryDevName.name: umCommonInventoryDevName
umCommonInventoryDevName.description: <write-operation is not provided for remote-side> This variable indicates the device name.

umCommonConfigTable.name: umCommonConfigTable
umCommonConfigTable.description: A table containing common config information.

umCommonConfigDate.name: umCommonConfigDate
umCommonConfigDate.description: This variable is used to define date information of the device. The format is MM/DD/YYYY. MM means month, DD is day, and YYYY stands for year. The range is from 01/01/1990 to 12/31/2100.

umCommonConfigTime.name: umCommonConfigTime
umCommonConfigTime.description: This variable is used to define time information of the device. The format is HH:MM:SS. HH means hour, MM is to indicate minute and SS is for second.

umCommonActionTable.name: umCommonActionTable
umCommonActionTable.description: A table containing actions to CPE.

umCommonActionDbSave.name: umCommonActionDbSave
umCommonActionDbSave.description: This variable is to initiate the VCDB command. 1: save

umCommonActionWarmStart.name: umCommonActionWarmStart
umCommonActionWarmStart.description: This value is to restart the device. TRUE (1): warm start

umCommonSnmpConfigTable.name: umCommonSnmpConfigTable
umCommonSnmpConfigTable.description: A table containing SNMP configuration information.

umCommonSnmpConfigIpAddress.name: umCommonSnmpConfigIpAddress
umCommonSnmpConfigIpAddress.description: This variable is to indicate IP address of the device.

umCommonSnmpConfigIpSubnetMask.name: umCommonSnmpConfigIpSubnetMask
umCommonSnmpConfigIpSubnetMask.description: This variable is to define the subnet mask of the IP address of the device.

umCommonSnmpConfigIpGatewayIp.name: umCommonSnmpConfigIpGatewayIp
umCommonSnmpConfigIpGatewayIp.description: This variable is to define the gateway IP address of the device.

umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress1.name: umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress1
umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress1.description: This variable is to define the IP address where the manager receives trap.

umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum1.name: umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum1
umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum1.description: This variable is to define the UDP port number where the manager receives trap. The possible values are: 162 (default) 62000 62001 62002

umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress2.name: umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress2
umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpAddress2.description: This variable is to define the IP address where the manager receives trap.

umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum2.name: umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum2
umCommonSnmpConfigTrapIpPortNum2.description: This variable is to define the UDP port number where the manager receives trap. The possible values are: 162 (default) 62000 62001 62002

umSdslConfigTable.name: umSdslConfigTable
umSdslConfigTable.description: A table containing Sdsl configuration information.

umSdslConfigNEType.name: umSdslConfigNEType
umSdslConfigNEType.description: This variable is to set this STU-C or STU-R configuration. (0): STU-C (LT mode) (1): STU-R (NT mode)

umSdslConfigRateAdaptive.name: umSdslConfigRateAdaptive
umSdslConfigRateAdaptive.description: This variable is to enable/disable the rate adaptive configuration. (0): Fixed (1): Adaptive

umSdslConfigDataRate.name: umSdslConfigDataRate
umSdslConfigDataRate.description: This variable is to set data rate (N*64k) of Sdsl. If Rate Adaptive is TRUE, the value is invalid till Rate Adaptive is FALSE.

umSdslResetPerformance.name: umSdslResetPerformance
umSdslResetPerformance.description: This value is to reset performance register. 1: reset all current performance data 2: reset current ES 3: reset current SES 4: reset current UAS 5: reset all history performance data 6: reset history ES 7: reset history SES 8: reset history UAS

umSdslTimeElapsed.name: umSdslTimeElapsed
umSdslTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current error-measurement period.

umSdslValidIntervals.name: umSdslValidIntervals
umSdslValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought on-line within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the since interface has been online.

umSdslThresholdTable.name: umSdslThresholdTable
umSdslThresholdTable.description: A table containing MSDSL configuration information.

umSdslThreshold15mES.name: umSdslThreshold15mES
umSdslThreshold15mES.description: This variable defines the 15-minute threshold of ES.

umSdslThreshold15mSES.name: umSdslThreshold15mSES
umSdslThreshold15mSES.description: This variable defines the 15-minute threshold of SES.

umSdslThreshold15mUAS.name: umSdslThreshold15mUAS
umSdslThreshold15mUAS.description: This variable defines the 15-minute threshold of UAS.

umSdslThreshold24hES.name: umSdslThreshold24hES
umSdslThreshold24hES.description: This variable defines the 24-hour threshold of ES.

umSdslThreshold24hSES.name: umSdslThreshold24hSES
umSdslThreshold24hSES.description: This variable defines the 24-hour threshold of SES.

umSdslThreshold24hUAS.name: umSdslThreshold24hUAS
umSdslThreshold24hUAS.description: This variable defines the 24-hour threshold of UAS.

umSdslThresholdSNRMargin.name: umSdslThresholdSNRMargin
umSdslThresholdSNRMargin.description: This variable indicates the SNR margin threshold of the Sdsl line. 1~15: valid value

umSdslThresholdLoopAttenuation.name: umSdslThresholdLoopAttenuation
umSdslThresholdLoopAttenuation.description: This variable indicates the Loop Attenuation threshold of the Sdsl line. 1~127:

umSdslPmCurrentUAS.name: umSdslPmCurrentUAS
umSdslPmCurrentUAS.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by an Sdsl during the current interval.

umSdslPmIntervalEntry.name: umSdslPmIntervalEntry
umSdslPmIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the Sdsl Interval table.

umSdslPmIntervalIndex.name: umSdslPmIntervalIndex
umSdslPmIntervalIndex.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval.

umSdslPmIntervalES.name: umSdslPmIntervalES
umSdslPmIntervalES.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one interval.

umSdslPmIntervalSES.name: umSdslPmIntervalSES
umSdslPmIntervalSES.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one interval.

umSdslPmIntervalUAS.name: umSdslPmIntervalUAS
umSdslPmIntervalUAS.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one interval.

umSdslPmCurrentDayTable.description: The Sdsl PM Current Day table. (0:00AM ~ the last completed quarter)

umSdslPmCurrentDayEntry.name: umSdslPmCurrentDayEntry
umSdslPmCurrentDayEntry.description: An entry in the Sdsl Pm Current Day table.

umSdslPmCurrentDayES.name: umSdslPmCurrentDayES
umSdslPmCurrentDayES.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl during the Current Day.

umSdslPmCurrentDaySES.name: umSdslPmCurrentDaySES
umSdslPmCurrentDaySES.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl during the Current Day.

umSdslPmCurrentDayUAS.name: umSdslPmCurrentDayUAS
umSdslPmCurrentDayUAS.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by an Sdsl during the Current Day.

umSdslPmDayEntry.name: umSdslPmDayEntry
umSdslPmDayEntry.description: An entry in the Sdsl Pm Day table.

umSdslPmDayIndex.name: umSdslPmDayIndex
umSdslPmDayIndex.description: A number between 1 and 7, where 1 is the most recently completed day and 7 is the least recently completed day.

umSdslPmDayES.name: umSdslPmDayES
umSdslPmDayES.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one day.

umSdslPmDaySES.name: umSdslPmDaySES
umSdslPmDaySES.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one day.

umSdslPmDayUAS.name: umSdslPmDayUAS
umSdslPmDayUAS.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by an Sdsl in one day.

umSdslTestTable.name: umSdslTestTable
umSdslTestTable.description: A table containing SHDSL testing function.

umSdslTestLoopback.name: umSdslTestLoopback
umSdslTestLoopback.description: This value is to set loopback. 0: Release 2: Loopback toward Network

umSdslTestPattern.name: umSdslTestPattern
umSdslTestPattern.description: This variable is used to set test pattern. 1: 511 2: 2047 3: PRBS Support Eoc Version 1.02 (23/04/2002)

umSdslTestPeriod.name: umSdslTestPeriod
umSdslTestPeriod.description: This variable is used to get/set test period in second. A value of 0 means non-stop testing.

umSdslTestStart.name: umSdslTestStart
umSdslTestStart.description: This value is to start or stop testing(only local). TRUE (1): Start FALSE (2): Stop

umSdslTestInsertOneBitError.name: umSdslTestInsertOneBitError
umSdslTestInsertOneBitError.description: This variable is used to initiate pause test pattern. This is used in error insertion application. (1) Insert error rate(rate= 10E-1)

umSdslTestElapsedTime.name: umSdslTestElapsedTime
umSdslTestElapsedTime.description: This variable is to indicate elapsed time of testing in second.

umSdslTestErrCount.name: umSdslTestErrCount
umSdslTestErrCount.description: This variable is to indicate error count of testing.

umSdslTestErrRate.name: umSdslTestErrRate
umSdslTestErrRate.description: This variable is to indicate error rate of testing, which is 'a.bcx10E(-d)', a, b, c: 0..9, d: 1..9.

umSdslV35ConfigTable.name: umSdslV35ConfigTable
umSdslV35ConfigTable.description: The config table contains Ne config items.

umSdslV35ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the config table

umSdslV35ConfigCurrentDataRate.description: This variable is to get current data rate (N*64k) of Sdsl V35.

umSdslV35ConfigCurrentTimingSrc.name: umSdslV35ConfigCurrentTimingSrc
umSdslV35ConfigCurrentTimingSrc.description: This variable is to get the current timing source of the system. 0: internal 1: from loop (SDSL) 2: from DTE (V.35)

umSdslV35ConfigTimingSrc.name: umSdslV35ConfigTimingSrc
umSdslV35ConfigTimingSrc.description: This variable is to get/set the setted timing source of the system. 0: internal 1: from loop (SDSL) 2: from DTE (V.35)

umSdslV35DTEEntry.name: umSdslV35DTEEntry
umSdslV35DTEEntry.description: An entry in the alarm table

umSdslV35DTEStatus.name: umSdslV35DTEStatus
umSdslV35DTEStatus.description: The variable represents which port reports the DTE Status. (bit) 0 : RTS 1 : CTS 2 : DCD 3 : DSR

umSdslV35DTERTS.name: umSdslV35DTERTS
umSdslV35DTERTS.description: The variable represents which port reports the RTS Config Status. 0 : RTS from DTE 1 : RTS Permanent On

umSdslV35TailFunc.name: umSdslV35TailFunc
umSdslV35TailFunc.description: The variable represents tail function switch. 0 : Tail off 1 : Tail on

umSdslV35LoopbackEntry.name: umSdslV35LoopbackEntry
umSdslV35LoopbackEntry.description: An entry in the Sdsl Testing table.

umSdslV35Loopback.name: umSdslV35Loopback
umSdslV35Loopback.description: This value is to set loopback. 0: Release 1: Toward DTE Loop 2: Toward Network Loop 3: Initial in-band Loop (V.54)

umSdslV35AlarmTable.name: umSdslV35AlarmTable
umSdslV35AlarmTable.description: The alarm table contains alarm event history.

umSdslV35AlarmEntry.name: umSdslV35AlarmEntry
umSdslV35AlarmEntry.description: An entry in the alarm table

umSdslV35ClearAlarmHistory.name: umSdslV35ClearAlarmHistory
umSdslV35ClearAlarmHistory.description: The variable initiate the clear alarm history action(Set 1).

umSdslV35AlarmStatus.name: umSdslV35AlarmStatus
umSdslV35AlarmStatus.description: The variable initiate the current alarm status. (bit) bit0: Loss of SDSL synchronization word (LOSW) bit1: (SDSL) ES exceed day threshold bit2: (SDSL) ES exceed quarter threshold bit3: (SDSL) SES exceed day threshold bit4: (SDSL) SES exceed quarter threshold bit5: (SDSL) UAS exceed day threshold bit6: (SDSL) UAS exceed quarter threshold bit7: (SDSL) SNR exceed threshold bit8: (SDSL) Loop Attuattion exceed threshold bit9~31: Reserved DataType = 72

umLiuTable.name: umLiuTable
umLiuTable.description: The LIU table. The LIU attributes regarding configuration and performance are defined in RFC1406.

umLiuEntry.name: umLiuEntry
umLiuEntry.description: An entry in the LIU table.

umLiuE1Transparent.name: umLiuE1Transparent
umLiuE1Transparent.description: This value gets/sets the E1 Transparency. Disable(0), Enable (1)

umLiuLineDrive.name: umLiuLineDrive
umLiuLineDrive.description: This variable is to define the value of line drive. 75_Ohm(0), 120_Ohm(1)

umLiuIdleCodeword.name: umLiuIdleCodeword
umLiuIdleCodeword.description: This variable represents the value of idle code word. But the write-operation is preserved for future use. If you take write-operation, <Generic error> will be returned.

umLiuE1SlotMap.name: umLiuE1SlotMap
umLiuE1SlotMap.description: This table defines the corresponding customer equipment interface for each time slot of network interface. Each bit represents one time slot. '1' stands for occupied. The leftmost bit represents time slot 31, and rightmost bit represents time slot 0.

umLiuResetPerformance.name: umLiuResetPerformance
umLiuResetPerformance.description: This value is to reset performance register for this port. 1: reset all current performance data 2: reset current LCV 3: reset current PCV 4: reset current ES 5: reset current SES 6: reset current SEFS 7: reset current UAS 8: reset current CSS 9: reset current DM 10: reset current CS 11: reset current FBE 51: reset all history performance data 52: reset history LCV 53: reset history PCV 54: reset history ES 55: reset history SES 56: reset history SEFS 57: reset history UAS 58: reset history CSS 59: reset history DM 60: reset history CS 61: reset history FBE

umLiuTestTable.name: umLiuTestTable

umLiuTestEntry.name: umLiuTestEntry
umLiuTestEntry.description: An entry in the LIU Test table.

umLiuLoopbackConfig.name: umLiuLoopbackConfig
umLiuLoopbackConfig.description: This value is to set LIU loopback. 0: release 1: payload loopback 2: line loopback 3: local loopback

umLiuLoopbackStatus.name: umLiuLoopbackStatus
umLiuLoopbackStatus.description: This value is to indicate the LIU loopback status. 0: released 1: payload loopback 2: line loopback 3: local loopback

umLiuTestPattern.name: umLiuTestPattern
umLiuTestPattern.description: This variable is used to set test pattern. 1: 2E15-1_PRBS 3: 2047

umLiuTestPeriod.name: umLiuTestPeriod
umLiuTestPeriod.description: This variable is used to set test period in second. A value of 0 means non-stop testing.

umLiuTestStart.name: umLiuTestStart
umLiuTestStart.description: This value is to start or stop testing. 1: Start 2: Stop

umLiuInsertedErrorRate.name: umLiuInsertedErrorRate

umLiuElapsedTime.name: umLiuElapsedTime
umLiuElapsedTime.description: This variable is to indicate elapsed time of testing.

umLiuTestErrCount.name: umLiuTestErrCount

umLiuTestErrRate.name: umLiuTestErrRate
umLiuTestErrRate.description: This variable is to indicate error rate of testing, which is 'a.bcx10E(-d)', a, b, c: 0..9, d: 1..9.
